[The same report was communicated by Sabine Zentis
<cvlonghorns@aol.com>.

It appears that human and livestock anthrax is continuing virtually
unabated as in previous years. A parallel report on bdnews24
(http://www.bdnews24.com/details.php?id=203983&cid=13) has the
village livestock being vaccinated. The ages of 13 of the16 people
affected are: 24, 25 (x2), 30 (x2), 35 (x3), 40 (x3), 55, and 60, the
ages of people one would expect to be involved in slaughtering and
butchering animals.

Rajshahi district and Rajshahi can be seen on the maps at
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/bangladesh_pol96.jpg
and http://healthmap.org/r/1a5C. - Mod.MHJ]
